## Plan

**Approach:** Add a NEW top-level `etude import` cobra command that reconstructs
etude runs from historical GitHub PRs via the authenticated `gh` CLI (NO GitHub
token). Each merged/closed PR maps to one run with exactly two stages: a
final-diff artifact and a PR-body artifact. The plan ENCODES THE HONEST
LIMITATION from BRIEF.md:315-325,416-423 — old PRs reliably yield only the final
diff + PR body, so imported runs are useful for benching `review`/`docs` skills
but NOT `plan`/`implement` (first drafts were never saved). We do NOT fabricate
plan/implement stages. We REUSE the runmanifest + capture-run writing path
(content-addressing, create-only ref write) rather than reinventing it. gh is an
external dependency, so a `gh`-runner interface (mirroring the retro generate
injected-generator seam at internal/cli/retro.go:793-801) makes tests hermetic.

### Command surface

```
etude import --from-github --repo <owner/name> --last N [flags]
```

Flags (decided):
- `--from-github` (bool, required for v1) — source selector. v1 supports only
  GitHub; the flag is explicit so a future `--from-gitlab` etc. is additive.
  If absent: error "exactly one source is required (--from-github)".
- `--repo <owner/name>` (string, required) — validated as `<owner>/<name>`
  (each segment non-empty, no spaces/slashes beyond the single separator).
- `--last N` (int, default 50) — matches BRIEF.md:386 `--last 50`. Reject N<1.
- `--state merged|closed|all` (string, default `merged`) — passed through to
  `gh pr list --state`. Default merged because only merged PRs carry a stable
  merge commit (the run's git_sha anchor); for `closed`/`all`, PRs lacking a
  merge commit are SKIPPED with a warning (no git_sha to anchor on).
- `--dry-run` (bool, default false) — fetch + map + print what WOULD be imported
  (run_id, pr#, git_sha, occurred_at, skip/exists reason) to stdout; write
  NOTHING to refs.
- `--message <msg>` (string) — optional commit message override (mirrors
  capture-run, internal/cli/capture_run.go:137); default per-run message below.

Registered in internal/cli/root.go:36-48 via `cmd.AddCommand(newImportCommand(out, errOut))`.

### gh integration (NO token) — exact calls + fields

Confirmed working with gh 2.88.1 against a live repo (cli/cli):

1. List PRs (one call, JSON):
   ```
   gh pr list --repo <owner/name> --state <state> --limit <N> \
     --json number,title,body,mergedAt,mergeCommit,author,url,state
   ```
   Returns a JSON array; each element has: `number` (int), `title` (string),
   `body` (string), `mergedAt` (RFC3339 string, "" or null when not merged),
   `mergeCommit.oid` (40-hex string, null when no merge commit), `author.login`
   (string), `url` (string), `state` (string: "MERGED"/"CLOSED"/"OPEN").
   (Confirmed: these exact fields all populate. `reviews` is also available on
   the list `--json` set but is NOT needed — review TEXT is not reconstructible
   from the list and is out of scope; we record only diff + body.)

2. Final diff per PR (one call each, raw text):
   ```
   gh pr diff <number> --repo <owner/name>
   ```
   Emits the unified diff on stdout, exit 0 on success, exit 1 + a clear stderr
   message ("could not find pull request diff: HTTP 404 ...") on failure.
   (Confirmed both success and the non-zero failure exit.)

gh-not-installed / not-authed handling (NO token fallback):
- Before any fetch, run `gh auth status` once. If `gh` is not on PATH
  (exec.LookPath fails) OR `gh auth status` exits non-zero, return a CLEAR
  actionable error and exit non-zero, e.g.:
  `gh CLI is required and must be authenticated; install gh and run 'gh auth login' (etude import uses gh, not a GitHub token)`.
- Per-PR `gh pr diff` failure: by default skip that PR with a warning to stderr
  and continue (one bad PR must not abort a --last 50 import); a `gh pr list`
  failure (whole-fetch) is fatal.

### PR -> run manifest mapping (one PR = one run)

| Field | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| run_id | `gh-<owner>-<repo>-pr<number>` | Sanitized: each `/`,`.` etc. in owner/repo replaced so the id satisfies `runmanifest.IsValidRunID` (manifest.go:675; allowed charset `[A-Za-z0-9_.-]`, no leading/trailing dot, no `..`, no `.lock`). Stable + collision-safe (PR# is unique per repo). |
| git_sha | `mergeCommit.oid` | The PR merge commit; the repo state anchor for replay. Validated 40/64-hex (validateGitSHA, capture.go:304). PRs with no merge commit are SKIPPED. |
| occurred_at | `mergedAt` (RFC3339) | REUSE the manifest OccurredAt field (8hq.2; manifest.go:43-47, set like retro.go:758) so `etude log` places imported runs at their real merge time, not import time. |
| created | import time (now, UTC) | Capture time, as everywhere. |
| workflow / workflow_version | `github-import` / `github-import-v1` | Distinct constants so imported runs are queryable/distinguishable from manual/live runs. |
| refs | `{pr: "<number>", repo: "<owner/name>", source: "github", url: "<pr url>", author: "<login>"}` | All string values (BRIEF.md:293). Keys validated by validateRefsMap (capture_run.go:440). NOTE: refs values are NOT charset-restricted (only keys are), so `<owner/name>` and the URL are valid ref VALUES. |
| producer.harness | `{name: "github-import", version: "<gh version>"}` | Records the import path as the producer harness. |
| producer.model | "" | No model — these are human-authored historical artifacts, not LLM output. Empty model is valid per the manifest schema. |
| producer.skill | `{id: "github-import", repo: "github-import", version: "github-import"}` | skill.id/repo/version are all REQUIRED non-empty by validateStage (manifest.go:403-411), so we set sentinel values. |

Stages (exactly two; honest model):
1. stage `implement`, produced_by `import`, output role `diff`, media_type
   `text/x-diff; charset=utf-8` (inferMediaType handles `.diff`, capture.go:608),
   content = `gh pr diff` output. (Role `diff` matches the BRIEF implement
   stage `produces: diff`, BRIEF.md:113.)
2. stage `review`, produced_by `import`, output role `review`, media_type
   `text/markdown; charset=utf-8`, content = the PR `body`. (PR body is the
   closest historical analog to a review/docs artifact, BRIEF.md:422.)

produced_by is the sentinel `import` (a valid identifier; distinguishes these
from `original`/`replay`/`retro`). The LIMITATION is encoded structurally
(only diff + body stages exist; no `plan` stage, no first-draft `implement`
artifact) AND documented in docs/import.md (below). A PR with an EMPTY body
still produces the diff stage but SKIPS the review stage (empty artifact would
be meaningless); a PR with an empty diff (rare) skips the diff stage. A PR that
ends up with zero stages is skipped with a warning (a manifest requires >=1
stage, manifest.go:226).

### Reuse-capture-run approach

REUSE, do not reinvent:
- `artifactstore.New()` + `store.AddContent(role, mediaType, content)` for
  content-addressing (as capture_run.go:210, addFileArtifactFromPath:373).
- `runmanifest.ArtifactFromManifestArtifact` to build ArtifactRefs.
- `runmanifest.WriteManifestTree(ctx, store, "refs/etude/runs/", manifest,
  files, refstore.WriteOptions{Message})` with ExpectedOld="" — the create-only
  path (capture_run.go:241-249). On `refstore.ErrRefExists`, treat as
  "already imported, skip" (NOT a fatal error — see idempotency).
- Constants/helpers from capture.go: `validateGitSHA`, `inferMediaType`,
  `validateCLIIdentifier`, `validateRefsMap`.
The PR->Stage assembly is NEW (no file paths; content comes from gh, not disk),
so we add a small `buildImportStage(role, mediaType string, content []byte,
gitSHA, now)` helper rather than overloading capture-run's path-based
`buildStage`. No extraction from capture_run.go is required; the shared writing
core already lives in `runmanifest.WriteManifestTree`.

### Idempotency + safety

- Create-only writes (ExpectedOld=""). A PR whose run ref
  `refs/etude/runs/gh-<owner>-<repo>-pr<number>` already exists is SKIPPED with
  an informational line ("pr 123 already imported as <run_id>, skipping"), NOT
  an error. So re-running `--last N` never clobbers and is safely repeatable
  (matches capture-run's create-only guarantee, refstore.go:65-68).
- Read-only against GitHub: only `gh pr list` / `gh pr diff` / `gh auth status`
  (no `gh pr edit`, no `gh api -X POST`). No writes to GitHub.
- Writes ONLY `refs/etude/runs/*` locally. Does NOT auto-push (matches
  capture/capture-run, which never push; the user runs `etude sync` separately,
  BRIEF.md:191-194). Documented in docs/import.md.
- `--dry-run` writes nothing.
- Summary line at end: "imported X, skipped Y (already present), skipped Z (no
  merge commit / empty), errors E".

